    {
      "name": "withdraw_v2",
      "docs": [
        "JoinSplit withdrawal: spend one note, create one change note.",
        "",
        "Proves in zero-knowledge: inAmount = publicWithdrawalAmount + outAmount",
        "Fee is deducted from recipient payout — vault releases exactly publicWithdrawalAmount:",
        "recipient receives: public_withdrawal_amount - fee_amount",
        "relayer receives:   fee_amount",
        "vault releases:     public_withdrawal_amount (= denomination)",
        "",
        "This means a 3.6 SOL deposit can drain exactly: 3×1 SOL + 6×0.1 SOL, no dust.",
        "",
        "# Arguments",
        "* `proof`                    — 256-byte Groth16 proof",
        "* `nullifier_hash`           — Reveals nullifier (Poseidon(1)(inNullifier)), prevents double-spend",
        "* `root`                     — Merkle root the input note is proven against",
        "* `public_withdrawal_amount` — Denomination released from vault (public)",
        "* `fee_amount`               — Protocol fee deducted from recipient payout (public)",
        "* `out_commitment`           — Change note commitment (new Merkle leaf)",
        "* `recipient_high/low`       — Recipient pubkey split into 16-byte halves",
        "* `relayer_high/low`         — Relayer pubkey split (binds proof to specific relayer)",
        "* `memo_blob`                — Encrypted change note (zerok:v2: prefix), in tx memo"
      ],
      "discriminator": [
